---
description: A reused component must look identical everywhere it appears
alwaysApply: true
---

# Consistent Components

When the same component (chart builder, card, button, badge…) is reused across
views, it must render with the same proportions, spacing and styling in every
context. If it "looks different," treat it as a bug and fix the shared source, not
the one instance.

## SVG charts must not be squished

The chart builders draw into a `viewBox` with `preserveAspectRatio="none"`, so if
the `viewBox` is a different aspect ratio than the element box, the chart is
stretched non-uniformly. Keep the `viewBox` tracking the real element size — never
clamp its min width/height above the sizes real cards actually use.

## Mini-charts: match the reference's inner geometry

Size a mini-chart's wrapper so its *inner* drawing area equals the reference
instance. Example — the bullet's inner area is `H - padT - padB`; the gallery
bullet (labelled, 56px → 20px inner) and the KPI-card bullet (no label, so
`8 + 20 + 18 = 46px`) both resolve to a 20px inner area, so bar/track/axis match.

## When flagged more than once

If the user points at the same inconsistency again, stop patching instances: find
the shared builder/CSS and fix it there so every instance updates at once.
